---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import CodeSnippet from '../components/CodeSnippet.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main class="landing">
			<section class="hero">
				<p class="eyebrow">Global protocols for multi-agent LLM systems</p>
				<h1>Deadlock-free agent workflows, written once.</h1>
				<p class="hero-copy">
					ZipperGen is a Python DSL and runtime for structured multi-agent LLM coordination.
					Write one global protocol describing messages, actions, and decisions; ZipperGen
					projects it onto each agent and runs the result concurrently.
				</p>
				<div class="hero-actions">
					<a class="button primary" href="https://github.com/zippergen-io/zippergen">View on GitHub</a>
					<a class="button secondary" href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.17612">Read the paper</a>
					<a href="https://github.com/zippergen-io/paper-isola/tree/main/Lean">
						<img src="/lean-formalized.svg" alt="Lean formalized" height="34" />
					</a>
					<a href="https://github.com/zippergen-io/paper-isola/tree/main/Lean">
						<img src="/lean.svg" alt="Lean verified" height="34" />
					</a>
				</div>
				<p class="trust-note">Core projection theorems machine-checked in Lean 4.</p>
				<figure class="hero-shot">
					<img
						src="/zipperchat-screenshot.png"
						alt="ZipperChat showing a workflow execution as a live message sequence chart"
					/>
				</figure>
			</section>

			<section class="feature-grid" aria-label="Core properties">
				<article>
					<h2>Global first</h2>
					<p>Write the coordination once as a protocol instead of scattering it across agent prompts and callbacks.</p>
				</article>
				<article>
					<h2>Projected locally</h2>
					<p>Each lifeline receives the local program it needs: sends, receives, owned decisions, and tool calls.</p>
				</article>
				<article>
					<h2>Deadlock-free</h2>
					<p>If the workflow compiles, the coordination layer is structurally deadlock-free by construction.</p>
				</article>
			</section>

			<section class="split-section">
				<div>
					<p class="section-label">Tiny workflow</p>
					<h2>Branching has an owner.</h2>
					<p>
						The annotation <code>@ Editor</code> says that Editor owns the decision. ZipperGen
						generates the control communication needed by the other lifelines.
					</p>
				</div>
				<CodeSnippet
					code={`@workflow
def write_tweet(topic: str @ User) -> str:
    User(topic) >> Writer(topic)
    Writer: tweet = draft(topic)
    Writer(tweet) >> Editor(tweet)
    Editor: approved = approve(tweet)

    if approved @ Editor:
        Editor(tweet) >> User(tweet)
    else:
        Editor(tweet) >> Writer(tweet)
        Writer: tweet = revise(tweet)
        Writer(tweet) >> User(tweet)

    return tweet @ User`}
				/>
			</section>

			<section class="bands">
				<div>
					<h2>Causal runtime guards</h2>
					<p>
						When locally received data can be stale, guards can read the latest causally visible
						state instead of a sequential log. Vector clocks and message-carried views make the
						guard result depend on the asynchronous communication structure.
					</p>
					<CodeSnippet
						code={`latest_device_on = Y[Device](
    atom(lambda env: env.get("on", False), src="on")
)

if latest_device_on @ Indicator:
    ...`}
					/>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h2>Unordered receives</h2>
					<p>
						Co-regions let a receiver accept independent messages in whichever order they arrive,
						while preserving FIFO order on each channel.
					</p>
					<CodeSnippet
						code={`with coregion:
    Analyst_A(a) >> Collector(a_report)
    Analyst_B(b) >> Collector(b_report)`}
					/>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="quick-start">
				<div>
					<p class="section-label">Try it locally</p>
					<h2>No service required for the first examples.</h2>
					<p>
						The built-in mock backend returns placeholder model outputs, so examples can be run
						without API keys. Switch to OpenAI, Mistral, or Claude with one configuration line
						when you want real model calls.
					</p>
				</div>
				<CodeSnippet
					lang="bash"
					code={`git clone https://github.com/zippergen-io/zippergen.git
cd zippergen
pip install -e .

python examples/coregion.py
python examples/cpl_test.py
python examples/write_tweet.py`}
				/>
			</section>

			<section class="formal-section">
				<p class="section-label">Formal foundation</p>
				<h2>Based on Message Sequence Charts.</h2>
				<p>
					The projection from a global protocol to per-agent local programs is syntax-directed,
					and deadlock-freedom follows by structural induction; no runtime checking required.
					The core theorems are in the paper and machine-checked in Lean 4.
				</p>
				<p>
					Bollig, Függer, Nowak. <em>Provable Coordination for LLM Agents via Message Sequence Charts.</em>
					<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.17612">arXiv:2604.17612 [cs.PL]</a>
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="cta-section">
				<h2>Build inspectable agent workflows.</h2>
				<p>
					Start from the examples, inspect the generated message sequence chart, and decide whether
					global protocols fit your agent system.
				</p>
				<div class="hero-actions">
					<a class="button primary" href="https://github.com/zippergen-io/zippergen">Get the code</a>
					<a class="button secondary" href="/about">About the project</a>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.landing {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: none;
		padding: 0;
	}

	.landing :global(pre) {
		margin: 0;
	}

	.hero,
	.feature-grid,
	.split-section,
	.bands,
	.quick-start,
	.formal-section,
	.cta-section {
		width: min(1120px, calc(100% - 2rem));
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.hero {
		padding: 5.5rem 0 3rem;
	}

	.eyebrow,
	.section-label {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		color: #9a6700;
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0;
		text-transform: uppercase;
	}

	.hero h1 {
		max-width: 850px;
		margin: 0;
		font-size: clamp(2.15rem, 5vw, 4.25rem);
		line-height: 1.02;
	}

	.hero-copy {
		max-width: 760px;
		margin: 1.35rem 0 0;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		font-size: 1.16rem;
		line-height: 1.65;
	}

	.hero-actions {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		align-items: center;
		margin-top: 1.6rem;
	}

	.button {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		min-height: 2.75rem;
		padding: 0 1.1rem;
		border-radius: 6px;
		font-weight: 600;
		text-decoration: none;
	}

	.button.primary {
		background: rgb(var(--black));
		color: white;
	}

	.button.secondary {
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--gray), 0.28);
		background: white;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}

	.hero-actions img {
		display: block;
		border-radius: 0;
	}

	.trust-note {
		margin: 0.75rem 0 0;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		font-size: 0.9rem;
	}

	.hero-shot {
		margin: 3rem 0 0;
	}

	.hero-shot img {
		display: block;
		width: 100%;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--gray), 0.2);
		border-radius: 8px;
		box-shadow: 0 22px 55px rgba(19, 31, 45, 0.12);
	}

	.feature-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1rem;
		padding: 1rem 0 3rem;
	}

	.feature-grid article {
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--gray), 0.18);
		border-radius: 8px;
		background: white;
		padding: 1.15rem;
	}

	.feature-grid h2,
	.bands h2,
	.quick-start h2,
	.formal-section h2,
	.cta-section h2,
	.split-section h2 {
		font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
	}

	.feature-grid h2 {
		margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
		font-size: 1.25rem;
	}

	.feature-grid p,
	.bands p,
	.quick-start p,
	.formal-section p,
	.cta-section p,
	.split-section p {
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}

	.split-section,
	.quick-start {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.78fr) minmax(0, 1.22fr);
		gap: 2rem;
		align-items: start;
		padding: 4rem 0;
	}

	.bands {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1.25rem;
		padding: 4rem 0;
	}

	.bands > div {
		border-radius: 8px;
		background: #f8fafc;
		padding: 1.35rem;
	}

	.bands .code-snippet {
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	.formal-section,
	.cta-section {
		padding: 4rem 0;
	}

	.formal-section p,
	.cta-section p {
		max-width: 760px;
	}

	.cta-section {
		padding-bottom: 5rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 840px) {
		.hero {
			padding-top: 3.25rem;
		}

		.feature-grid,
		.split-section,
		.bands,
		.quick-start {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.split-section,
		.bands,
		.quick-start,
		.formal-section,
		.cta-section {
			padding: 2.75rem 0;
		}
	}
</style>
